          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "PhoP-regulated transcription is redox-sensitive, being activated when the periplasm becomes more reducing. MgrB acts between DsbA/DsbB and PhoP/PhoQ in this pathway. Represses PhoP/PhoQ signaling, possibly by binding to the periplasmic domain of PhoQ, altering its activity and that of downstream effector PhoP"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
